There are three differences between Eq. 2 and the corresponding equation of Connor
and Stevens: in the Connor-Stevens equation there are two potassium K activation
terms, the equilibrium potential of the A system is slightly different from VK, and
XA is raised to the fourth power. None of these differences will affect the qualitative
behavior of Eq. 2.

