We have observed that the R15 cell occasionally spontaneously alters its output from
a bursting to a beating mode. When the cell is in the beating mode, the injection of
hyperpolarizing current through the recording electrode will return the cell to a burst-
ing mode. Upon cessation of the current injection the cell returns to a beating mode.
Fig. 6 shows the results of one such experiment. By the application of ouabain, Junge
and Stephens (1973) have demonstrated that the beating mode of the R15 cell is asso-
ciated with the abolishment of the electrogenic pump current. For It = -0.14, Fig.
5 b, bottom trace, the spontaneous activity is abolished, due to the slow wave's state
point being moved to a lower stable equilibrium point. Thus the model is seen to ade-
quately predict the result ofexperiments.

